fields.description:
Change to Data Entry and QA apps to support the user changing their own password or updating 'how to contact' details.

Refer to comment thread for details, the changes previously closed 'not required' are:

1. add generic GA skin to the 'CAS Login Page'. There is no need for static text indicating login is for 'Floods' or 'landslide' data entry.
2. change the 'user:username' link in the top right corner of the header to include '(Maintain Account)'
3. on clicking the '(Maintain Account)' link, user is taken to the 'Change Details' page .../authentication-manager/main?execution=e1s4
4. at the 'Change Details' page, add text adjacent the 'Save' button: 'Note: if you update your password, you will need to log in again with your new password.'
5. at the 'Change Details' page, include a list of 'common home pages' that includes Floods Data Entry and Landslides Data Entry.

Lower priority:
6. if the user does any action that takes them outside the app (eg requests page outside the app domain), display a dialog box 'This will log you out. Do you wish to continue?'
